#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.19"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.19:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.19:0.2"
msgid "2. Nālandavagga "
msgstr "2. At Nālandā "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.19:0.3"
msgid "19. Sedakasutta "
msgstr "19. At Sedaka "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.169, sc1
msgctxt "sn47.19:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sumbhesu viharati sedakaṃ nāma sumbhānaṃ nigamo. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sumbhas, near the town of the Sumbhas called Sedaka. "

msgctxt "sn47.19:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.19:1.3"
msgid "“bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, caṇḍālavaṃsiko caṇḍālavaṃsaṃ ussāpetvā medakathālikaṃ antevāsiṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, an acrobat set up his bamboo pole and said to his apprentice Medakathālikā, "

msgctxt "sn47.19:1.4"
msgid "‘ehi tvaṃ, samma medakathālike, caṇḍālavaṃsaṃ abhiruhitvā mama uparikhandhe tiṭṭhāhī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Come now, dear Medakathālikā, climb up the bamboo pole and stand on my shoulders.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Comm tries to erase the students gender.
msgctxt "sn47.19:1.5"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, ācariyā’ti kho, bhikkhave, medakathālikā antevāsī caṇḍālavaṃsikassa paṭissutvā caṇḍālavaṃsaṃ abhiruhitvā ācariyassa uparikhandhe aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, teacher,’ she replied. She climbed up the bamboo pole and stood on her teacher’s shoulders. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.19:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, caṇḍālavaṃsiko medakathālikaṃ antevāsiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the acrobat said to Medakathālikā, "

msgctxt "sn47.19:1.7"
msgid "‘tvaṃ, samma medakathālike, mamaṃ rakkha, ahaṃ taṃ rakkhissāmi. "
msgstr "‘You look after me, dear Medakathālikā, and I’ll look after you. "

#. VAR: lābhañca → lābhe ca (bj)
msgctxt "sn47.19:1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ aññamaññaṃ guttā aññamaññaṃ rakkhitā sippāni ceva dassessāma, lābhañca lacchāma, sotthinā ca caṇḍālavaṃsā orohissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "That’s how, guarding and looking after each other, we’ll display our skill, collect our fee, and get down safely from the bamboo pole.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.19:1.9"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, medakathālikā antevāsī caṇḍālavaṃsikaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Medakathālikā said to her teacher, "

msgctxt "sn47.19:1.10"
msgid "‘na kho panetaṃ, ācariya, evaṃ bhavissati. "
msgstr "‘That’s not how it is, teacher! "

msgctxt "sn47.19:1.11"
msgid "Tvaṃ, ācariya, attānaṃ rakkha, ahaṃ attānaṃ rakkhissāmi. "
msgstr "You should look after yourself, and I’ll look after myself. "

msgctxt "sn47.19:1.12"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ attaguttā attarakkhitā sippāni ceva dassessāma, lābhañca lacchāma, sotthinā ca caṇḍālavaṃsā orohissāmā’”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how, guarding and looking after ourselves, we’ll display our skill, collect our fee, and get down safely from the bamboo pole.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.19:2.1"
msgid "“So tattha ñāyo”ti bhagavā etadavoca, “yathā medakathālikā antevāsī ācariyaṃ avoca. "
msgstr "That’s the way,” said the Buddha. “It’s just as Medakathālikā said to her teacher. "

msgctxt "sn47.19:2.2"
msgid "Attānaṃ, bhikkhave, rakkhissāmīti satipaṭṭhānaṃ sevitabbaṃ; "
msgstr "Thinking ‘I’ll look after myself,’ you should cultivate mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "sn47.19:2.3"
msgid "paraṃ rakkhissāmīti satipaṭṭhānaṃ sevitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "Thinking ‘I’ll look after others,’ you should cultivate mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "sn47.19:2.4"
msgid "Attānaṃ, bhikkhave, rakkhanto paraṃ rakkhati, paraṃ rakkhanto attānaṃ rakkhati. "
msgstr "Looking after yourself, you look after others; and looking after others, you look after yourself. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn47.19:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, attānaṃ rakkhanto paraṃ rakkhati? "
msgstr "And how do you look after others by looking after yourself? "

msgctxt "sn47.19:3.2"
msgid "Āsevanāya, bhāvanāya, bahulīkammena—"
msgstr "By development, cultivation, and practice of meditation. "

msgctxt "sn47.19:3.3"
msgid "evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attānaṃ rakkhanto paraṃ rakkhati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn47.19:3.4"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, paraṃ rakkhanto attānaṃ rakkhati? "
msgstr "And how do you look after yourself by looking after others? "

msgctxt "sn47.19:3.5"
msgid "Khantiyā, avihiṃsāya, mettacittatāya, anudayatāya—"
msgstr "By acceptance, harmlessness, love, and sympathy. "

msgctxt "sn47.19:3.6"
msgid "evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, paraṃ rakkhanto attānaṃ rakkhati. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.19:3.7"
msgid "Attānaṃ, bhikkhave, rakkhissāmīti satipaṭṭhānaṃ sevitabbaṃ; "
msgstr "Thinking ‘I’ll look after myself,’ you should cultivate mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "sn47.19:3.8"
msgid "paraṃ rakkhissāmīti satipaṭṭhānaṃ sevitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "Thinking ‘I’ll look after others,’ you should cultivate mindfulness meditation. "

msgctxt "sn47.19:3.9"
msgid "Attānaṃ, bhikkhave, rakkhanto paraṃ rakkhati, paraṃ rakkhanto attānaṃ rakkhatī”ti. "
msgstr "Looking after yourself, you look after others; and looking after others, you look after yourself.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.19:3.10"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

